      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Gear Pressure Angle</text> is the angle between the &apos;Line of Action&apos; and the Line Perpendicular to the Line-of-centers.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Gear Pressure Angle</text> is most easily appreciated when the gears are positioned so that the contact point coincides with the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Gear-Line-of-Centres" styleclass="VariableName-small">Line-of-centers</link>, as in the images above. The &apos;Line-of-Action&apos; and the perpendicular to &apos;Line-of-centers&apos; are shown for <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Gear Pressure Angles of 20º, 25,º &amp; 14.5º.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
